# a simple wrapper for PushOver

the wrapper holds a websocket connection to pushover. if a new message arrives, the message gets deleted and the provided API-URI gets called. simple as that

flags:
  -apiURI: the URI which gets called if a new message arrives
  -appName: your PushOver application name to listen (default "Pushover")
  -deviceID: your PushOver device ID
  -filter: regex String to filter the message by title
  -logFile: path to optinal log file
  -secret: your PushOver secret
